attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, SPARC, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai family, targeting MIPS32-based IoT devices. It features a comprehensive suite of attack vectors including UDP, TCP, HTTP, and specialized floods (OVH, PAKI, NUKE). Key indicators include raw socket packet crafting (makeIPPacket, checksum_tcp_udp), a command-and-control (C2) processing loop (processCmd), watchdog manipulation to prevent system reboots, and a hardcoded list of browser User-Agents for HTTP flooding. Relevant IOCs include /dev/watchdog interference and multiple flooding routines (sendTCP, sendUDP, sendHTTP).
